  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>2/20/15</Date>
    <Description>On behalf of Mohannad Murad, made the follow updates: added ODI_CUST_FU47_IND02_ENABLED and K_UPA_TYPE cals that were missing from this caldef. Also added units for RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_SMART_TOW cal that previously had no units shown.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>4/17/2015</Date>
    <Description>On behalf of Mohannad Murad, made the follow MY18 updates per updates in GIS-040 version 5.03: deleted ODI_CUST_FU47_IND02_ENABLED cal as it will no longer be needed for MY18, and added the new cal RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_RCTA_SYMBOLS in this caldef file.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>7/28/2015</Date>
    <Description>For clarity and consistency, updated the resolution and maximum values for the RVS_OVLAY_TRACK_WIDTH, RVS_STEER_REAR_AXLE_OFFSET, and RVS_STEER_SATURATION_ANGLE CALs to match the values already shown in the GIS-040 Spec.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>22SEP15</Date>
    <Description>Changed all Float cals to Integers because the GM Rear Guideline C algorithm software which exclusively requires scaled integers.   These values were incorrectly defined as Float calibrations in the initial release of this caldef.  </Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>12/1/2015</Date>
    <Description>Removed the following four CALs: 1.) RVS_CAMERA_DELTA_PITCH, 2.) RVS_CAMERA_DELTA_ROLL, 3.) RVS_CAMERA_DELTA_YAW, and 4.) RVS_CAMERA_DISP_BORDER_WIDTH from this CalDef file as these were CALs confirmed not to be needed for Info 3.0, and aren't CALs listed in the calibration section of the GIS-040 Spec.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>June 13, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef, made the following updates: 1.) Updated the RVS_OVLAY_NUM_DIST_MARKS CAL to change the Max and default value from 5 to 4 for FMVS111. Updated GIS-040A will also reflect this. 2.)  Updated the calibration default values within the RVS_UPA_CENTER_U_PIXEL_ARRAY CAL, and  updated the calibration default values within the RVS_UPA_CENTER_V_PIXEL_ARRAY CAL.  Deleted the existing RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_SMART_TOW enumeration CAL with Cal ID(_g3XiccAEEeO0R63G0HVPeg) because it was incorrectly being linked to the enumeration for the RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_GUIDELINES, therefore, needed to delete this existing calibration and create a new RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_SMART_TOW enumeration CAL (Cal ID:_8UVeYCylEeaQhflu2B0O3Q)) to link it to a new RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_SMART_TOW enumeration that needed to be added to the FrontRearCameraStatic.enumdef file with the possible enumeration options for this calibration to match the possible enuumeration options that were already being shown for this calibration in the GIS-040. Also, calibration description update only for the RVS_TEXT_LOCATION calibration to just clarify what the possible values that already shown in the GIS-040 are intended to represent for this calibration.   </Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>June 14, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Added the following calibrations for 2019 for Hitch View: RVS_SMART_TOW_OFF_HYSTERESIS, K_HITCH_VIEW_PAN_LEVEL_V, K_HITCH_VIEW_PAN_LEVEL_U, K_HITCH_VIEW_TILT_LEVEL, K_HITCH_VIEW_ZOOM_LEVEL, RVS_CENTLN_START_Y_OFFSET, RVS_CENTLN_HEIGHT, RVS_CENTLN_ENAB, RVS_CENTL_SHOW_VERT_BARS, SH_R_DYNAMIC_GUIDELINE_DELAY_TIME, and K_PAN_ZOOM_TILT.</Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>Oct 27, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Per email confirmation from Jonathan Beckwith on 10/26/2016, add low radio usage to RVS_SMART_TOW_OFF_HYSTERESIS calibration.</Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>Nov. 30, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Within FrontRearCameraStatic.caldef file, made the following updates for MY19 DIGITAL CAMERA CALIBRATIONS PER CR 1239588 AND REVISIONS TO GIS 40A V6.04: ADDED the following seventeen new calibrations: 1.) RVS_OVLAY_LINE_OFFSET, 2.) RVS_OVLAY_LINE_LENGTH, 3.) RVS_OVLAY_LINE_WIDTH, 4.) ANALOG_VS_DIGITAL, 5.) CROP_BOTTOM, 6.) CROP_TOP, 7.) CROP_RIGHT, 8.) CROP_LEFT, 9.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_4, 10.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_3, 11.) RVS_STD_VIEW_PAN_OFFSET_V, 12.) RVS_STD_VIEW_PAN_OFFSET_U, 13.) RVS_STD_VIEW_DISTORT_FACTOR, 14.) RVS_STD_VIEW_ZOOM_FACTOR, 15.) RVS_CAMERA_PIZEL_SIZE, 16.) RVS_CAMERA_RES_HEIGHT, and 17.) RVS_CAMERA_RES_WIDTH. Updated the default and resolution values for the RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_1 &amp;2 calibrations. Also, updated the default value for the K_HITCH_VIEW_ZOOM_LEVEL calibration. </Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>Jan. 20, 2017</Date>
    <Description>Add 4 more digital cals for low radio. RVS_VIEW_TOP_MARGIN;RVS_VIEW_SECANT_HEIGHT;RVS_VIEW_VIEW_HEIGHT;RVS_VIEW_HALF_ANGLE_OF_VIEW</Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>2/10/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file for RTC CR#: 1304082 added the new calibration called RVS_GUIDELINES_TRANSPARENCY.</Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>6/16/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the FrontRearCameraStatic.caldef made the following updates: 1.) Deleted previous version RVS_CAMERA_PIXEL_SIZE, RVS_STD_VIEW_ZOOM_FACTOR, RVS_STD_VIEW_ZOOM_FACTOR, and RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_3 calibrations that were incorrectly defined as integer type calibrations and should  have been defined as float type calibrations instead. To address this issue, recreated new calibrations for each of these four calibrations and defined each as a float type calibration and carried over the exact same calibration names and CalIDs that were originally used for these calibrations, 2.) Updated the calibration description of the existing RVS_SMART_TOW_OFF_HYSTERESIS calibration just to add additional clarification of the function of this calibration per the GIS-040, and 3.) Also, updated the usage field for all of the calibrations within the FrontRearCameraStatic.caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>9/30/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the FrontRearCameraStatic.caldef file, added GEM usage to the following calibrations within this caldef: (1.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_3, (2. ) RVS_STD_VIEW_DISTORT_FACTOR, (3.) RVS_STD_VIEW_ZOOM_FACTOR, (4.) RVS_CAMERA_PIZEL_SIZE, (5.) RVS_GUIDELINES_TRANSPARENCY, (6.) RVS_VIEW_HALF_ANGLE_OF_VIEW, (7.) RVS_VIEW_VIEW_HEIGHT, (8.) RVS_VIEW_SECANT_HEIGHT, (8.) RVS_VIEW_TOP_MARGIN, (9.)  RVS_OVLAY_LINE_OFFSET, (10.) RVS_OVLAY_LINE_LENGTH, (11.) RVS_OVLAY_LINE_WIDTH, (12.) ANALOG_VS_DIGITAL, (13.) CROP_BOTTOM, (14.) CROP_TOP, (15.) CROP_LEFT, (16.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_4, (17.) RVS_STD_VIEW_PAN_OFFSET_V, (18.) RVS_STD_VIEW_PAN_OFFSET_U, (19.) RVS_CAMERA_RES_HEIGHT, (20.) RVS_CAMERA_RES_WIDTH, (21.) K_HITCH_VIEW_ZOOM_LEVEL, (22.) RVS_SMART_TOW_OFF_HYSTERESIS, (23.) RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_SMART_TOW,(24.) .K_HITCH_VIEW_PAN_LEVEL_U, (25.)RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_RCTA_SYMBOLS, (26.) K_UPA_TYPE, (27.) RVS_RCTA_CENTER_U_PIXEL_1, (28.) RVS_RCTA_CENTER_V_PIXEL_2, (29.) RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_VIDEO, (30.) RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_GUIDELINES, (31.) RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_UPA_SYMBOLS, (32.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_1, (33.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_2, (34.) RVS_CAMERA_FOCAL_LENGTH_U, (35.) RVS_CAMERA_FOCAL_LENGTH_V, (36.) RVS_CAMERA_OFFSET_X, (37.) RVS_CAMERA_ROTATION_Y, (38.) RVS_CAMERA_ROTATION_Z, (39.) RVS_DISABLE_HYSTERESIS_SPEED, (40.) RVS_SMART_TOW_EXIT_TIME, (41.) RVS_OFF_HYSTERESIS, (42.) RVS_ON_HYSTERESIS, (43.) RVS_OVLAY_DELTA_DIST_MARKS, (44.) RVS_OVLAY_NUM_DIST_MARKS, (45.) RVS_OVLAY_TRACK_WIDTH, (46.) RVS_PRESENT_STATUS, (47.) RVS_STEER_INVERSE_FRONT_RATIO, (48,) RVS_STEER_INVERSE_REAR_RATIO, (49.)RVS_STEER_CENTER_HEIGHT_OFFSET, (50.) RVS_CENTLN_START_Y_OFFSET, (51.) RVS_CENTLN_HEIGHT, (52.) RVS_CENTLN_ENAB, (53.) RVS_CENTL_SHOW_VERT_BARS, (54.) SH_R_DYNAMIC_GUIDELINE_DELAY_TIME, (55.) RVS_STEER_CENTER_START_OFFSET, (56.) RVS_STEER_CENTER_OFFSET, (57.) RVS_STEER_CENTER_OFFSET, (58.) RVS_STEER_REAR_AXLE_OFFSET, (59.) RVS_STEER_SATURATION_ANGLE, (60.) RVS_STEER_WHEELBASE, (61.) RVS_STEERING_WHEEL_DELTA, (62.) RVS_TEXT_LOCATION, (63.) RVS_UPA_CENTER_V_PIXEL_ARRAY, (64.)RVS_UPA_CENTER_U_PIXEL_ARRAY, and (65.) RVS_APA_ICON_CENTER_U. Since these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>16</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the FrontRearCameraStatic.caldef removed the following four calibrations { 1.) RVS_CAMERA_PIXEL_SIZE, 2.) RVS_STD_VIEW_ZOOM_FACTOR, 3.) RVS_STD_VIEW_DISTORT_FACTOR, and 4.) RVS_CAMERA_DISTORT_COEF_3}   that were changed to a Float type calibration, and changed them back to Integer type calibrations to realign with how there currently defined in the GIS-040.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>17</Version>
    <Date>Jan 12 2018</Date>
    <Description>CR: 1579024 add 2 new binary cals for info 3.5: RVS_Image_Configuration and RVS_Hitchview_Configuration ; updated description for RVS_FEATURE_AVAIL_SMART_TOW and RVS_CENTLN_ENAB </Description>
    <Author>Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>18</Version>
