  <CalDefinition Description="Calibration is used to determine if the vehicle has a camera and also determines which type of camera.On/Off Option&#xA;If the RVS_ FEATURE_AVAIL_VIDEO=2  then the HMI module shall have a Front Camera Display request selection for the driver.  This will allow the driver to request the front camera on when the vehicle movement state is equal to forward and the vehicle speed is less than RVS_DISABLE_HYSTERESIS_SPEED (e.g. 7mph).  When the front camera view is selected by the driver  the HMI module shall send a GMLAN message (Display_Front_360_Camera_Req == 1) to the Video Processing Module to display the front camera view.  &#xA;If the RVS_ FEATURE_AVAIL_VIDEO=2  then the HMI module shall send a GMLAN message (VPM_Video_ICS_Disp_Status == 1) to the Video Processing Module when the VPM video signal is being displayed on the ICS.  When the ICS is NOT displaying the VPM video signal  then the HMI module shall send a GMLAN message (VPM_Video_ICS_Disp_Status == 0) to the Video Processing Module .&#xA;NOTE: When RVS_PRESENT_STATUS=2  HMIM software shall ignore rear camera cals - VPM controls camera features.&#xA;" Name="RVS_PRESENT_STATUS" References="GIS 40A" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_ysAbAE1AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>26AUG2013</Date>
      <Description>Initial import on from GIS-344 derived CSV file.  Original CALDS block=hmi_rr_view_camera_caln</Description>
      <Author>GIS-344 GIS-343</Author>
